Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1

Quick query:

When we say 'deprecate', do we mean that "/tasks" will go away or will just always be accessible by admin?

If we really mean /tasks will no longer exist: will someone beat us up for not being backwards compatible?

Patch Set 4:

Based on the current policies we follow, we can't really delete it entirely. However, we can disable it (even for admins... config option?) in the future and bump the API version and mark previous minor versions as deprecated.

(OT: Eventually, I'd love to evaluate the micro-versions concept, but I ain't got brain cycles for that right now)

Patch Set 4:

@Flavio

> we can't really delete it entirely

Yeah, that's my understanding.

It'll always be there, even though you don't want it. (Like nuclear waste).

Is it 100% accurate to say 'this API is going to be deprecated'?

(As you know, these grey areas confuse the hell out of me!)
